Subject: Indonesia at the 2004 Summer Olympics 
To: Juliana
Content:
Indonesia competed at the 2004 Summer Olympics in Athens, Greece. Men's individual: Women's individual: Men's 110 metre hurdles: Women's 5000 metres: Men's singles: Men's doubles: Women's doubles: Mixed doubles: Indonesia sent one boxer, a flyweight, to the 2004 Olympics. He lost his first bout. Flyweight (51kg) Women's K1 500 metres: Women's points race: Men's 90kg: Mia Audina, who won the silver medal in badminton at the 1996 Summer Olympics, has repeated that feat in the 2004 Olympics. Mia Audina was born in Indonesia, and competed for that country in the 1996 Olympic Games. She is now competing for the Netherlands.
